9. Huang CC, Liu CC, Chang YC, et al: Neurologic complications in children with enterovirus 71 infection. N Engl J Med. 1999; 341(13): 936-42; full article available at http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199909233411302.
10. Dietz V, Andrus J, Olive JM, et al: Epidemiology and clinical characteristics of acute flaccid paralysis associated with non-polio enterovirus isolation: the experience in the Americas. Bull World Health Organ. 1995; 73(5): 597-603; full article available at http://whqlibdoc.who.int/bulletin/1995/Vol73-No5/bulletin_1995_73%285%29_597-603.pdf.
11. Hayward JC, Gillespie SM, Kaplan KM, et al: Outbreak of poliomyelitis-like paralysis associated with enterovirus 71. Pediatr Infect Dis J. 1989; 8(9): 611-6; abstract available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2797956.
